6 An Act relating to wildlife; amending 29 O.S. 2021,

Section 2:
Section 3-103a, which relates to special permits for
7 designated species; allowing for certain special
permit; expanding opportunities to acquire special
8 permit; providing for wildlife without open season;
updating statutory language; and providing an
9 effective date.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 29 O.S. 2021, Section 3-103a, is
14 amended to read as follows:
15 Section 3-103a. The Oklahoma Wildlife Conservation Commission
16 may, by order, authorize the Department of Wildlife Conservation to
17 issue, in addition to regular permits issued under this title, up to
18 five (5) special permits each year for designated species. The
19 special permits, which may be co-branded in association with the
20 Governor, shall be sold at public auction or by sealed bid, raffle,
21 or lottery. In the case of mountain lions and wildlife for which no
22 open season currently exists, the permits shall be conducted by
23 raffle. The Department may contract with nonprofit organizations or
24 charitable causes to conduct the public auctions.
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1073 Page 1
1 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
2 Passed the Senate the 24th day of March, 2025.
